HEADWORD: Umbratical
<hw>Um*brat"ic*al</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧m*br⟦acr⟧t"⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>umbraticus</ets>, from <ets>umbra</ets>
shade. See <er>Umbrage</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the shade
or darkness; shadowy; unreal; secluded; retired.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
